text:
Hello, I'm Eric Shahan and I'm a student at Launchcode.
While I've always had an interest in technology, I have spent the last six months at Launchcode taking their Java Web Development course. This involved learning about Java, Javascript, Spring Boot, Thymeleaf, React, and how they can work together to create fullstack applications. These skills helped me work on the capstone project in my portfolio; Triangle Management.
In addition, I have spent a few college semesters at the Missouri University Of Science And Technology as a Computer Science student, and took some relevant courses there including Computer Science 1570 and Computer Engineering 2210.
I was encouraged to pursue professional development in technology by the time I spent in highschool pursuing it as a hobby. Many classes I took for fun had a background in tech, such as my robotics classes and my class on Javascript game development. In my spare time I even explored TI-Basic to program my calculator with games.

text:
I am Jean Olele and I have worked as a Professional Math And Science Tutor for Saint Louis community college from where i also got an Associate degree in General Transfert Study, Which led to to get Admission  a Junior Computer Science Student at the University of Missouri Saint Louis, Previous to that, i was not the best student in science, but i challenged myself to get to that Level And Even got Awarded as one of the best Tutor for the College in 2018.
I have Always been interested about programming but never Got to dive in the field and Fully invest Myself into it. In Fact, this is not my first time Applying for LaunchCode , but i had to keep on Trying and pushing.
I am currently working in the Optical Field as an inspector, Another way to challenge Myself and Learn something completely new and different. I like learning New Skills from scratch, Grow and become the best version of myself everyday.
Since May 2023 I have join the Full Stack Web development Program again, we have learned technologies such as JavaScript along with React, Java for the backend along with Springboot and Thymeleaf. We have also used MySql to manage the Database.
 My Team and I have decided to work on a Customer Relationship Management Application(CRM). Starting this Project from scratch can be intimidating , but with all the tools and knowledge we acquire from day one of class, i firmly believe this will be a great Opportunity to Sharpen my Skills. In my next career, as a mentioned before, i wish to continue growing, learning more and contribute as much as i could in the tech Industry to uplift others as well.
